# x402-Agent Framework

A lightweight Python framework for building autonomous AI agents that can pay for tools, APIs, and other agents in real-time using x402 micropayments.

## Overview

The x402-Agent Framework eliminates API key management and subscription friction by enabling pay-per-use interactions through HTTP 402 status codes and USDC payments on blockchain networks.

## Features

- **Autonomous Micropayments**: Agents automatically pay for API access using USDC
- **HTTP 402 Integration**: Seamless handling of payment-required responses
- **Multi-Agent Swarms**: Collaborative agents with cost-splitting capabilities
- **Deferred Payment Batching**: Efficient transaction batching to minimize gas costs
- **Multi-Blockchain Support**: Base Network primary, extensible to other networks
- **Simple Setup**: One-line agent creation with minimal configuration

## Installation

```bash
pip install x402-agent
```

## Quick Start

```python
from x402_agent import X402Agent

# Create an agent with your wallet and LLM
agent = X402Agent(llm=your_llm, wallet_key="your_private_key")

# Register tools
agent.register_tool("weather", "https://api.weather.com/v1/current")

# Run tasks - payments handled automatically
result = agent.run("Get the current weather in San Francisco")
```

## Requirements

- Python 3.8+
- Private key for Base Network wallet
- LLM provider (OpenAI, Anthropic, etc.)

## Documentation

Full documentation available at [docs.x402-agent.dev](https://docs.x402-agent.dev)

